<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,950,1286]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">
Diagnosis. Integument smooth or finely striated, with fine porosity in underlying strata. III-L-5 and IV-L-4–5 with 1–2 elongated distal setae. IV-L-5 with 4-5 robust ventral setae (
<figureCitation box="[826,893,985,1009]" captionStart="Figures 3–7" captionStartId="2.[155,227,2051,2073]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,427,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[189,1399,417,2003]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 3–7. Lebertia (Lebertia) fimbriata, male. 3. Palp. 4. Gnathosoma. 5. Genital field. 6. I-L-1–6. 7. IV-L-2–6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Numbers of swimming setae: III-L-5, 1-2; IV-L-4, 1-2; IV-L-5, 2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,950,1286]" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">
Description. Male. Idiosoma (
<figureCitation box="[516,616,1054,1078]" captionStart="Figures 1–2" captionStartId="1.[323,395,2059,2081]" captionTargetBox="[320,1270,1334,2009]" captionTargetId="figure-409@1.[265,1323,1328,2022]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–2. Lebertia (Lebertia) fimbriata, male. 1. Ventral view. 2. Dorsal view. Scale bars=100µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367274" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367274/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
). Color yellowish-brown. Idiosoma elliptical in outline. Integument smooth, 632 long and 496 wide. Coxal plates single group, 
<quantity box="[731,804,1089,1113]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.40462" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="553.0">553 in</quantity>
length and 
<quantity box="[946,1020,1089,1113]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.18618" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="467.0">467 in</quantity>
width, Cx-I ML 146, Cx-II ML 124, Cx-I/Cx-II ML ratio 1.17, posterior margin of Cx-II narrow, posterior width 29. Ib-Gf 276, Ib-Ap 521. Suture lines between Cx-III and Cx-IV not reaching to inner extremity but to 2/3 of plate. Cx-IV widest, with gently rounded sides. Gf length 168, width 126. Acetabula 3 pairs, first pair 
<quantity box="[723,782,1192,1217]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="50.0">50 in</quantity>
length, second 
<quantity box="[963,1022,1193,1217]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0413999999999999" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="41.0">41 in</quantity>
length, third 
<quantity box="[1179,1238,1193,1217]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.382" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" unit="in" value="33.0">33 in</quantity>
length (
<figureCitation box="[1335,1406,1193,1217]" captionStart="Figures 3–7" captionStartId="2.[155,227,2051,2073]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,427,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[189,1399,417,2003]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 3–7. Lebertia (Lebertia) fimbriata, male. 3. Palp. 4. Gnathosoma. 5. Genital field. 6. I-L-1–6. 7. IV-L-2–6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Ib U-shaped, depth 138, width 62. Excretory pore smooth. Gnathosoma ventral margin with a indentation beneath mouth opening. Gnathosoma L 112, chelicera L 201.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367274" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5367274" box="[323,1304,2059,2081]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367274/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="55" startId="1.[323,395,2059,2081]" targetBox="[320,1270,1334,2009]" targetPageId="1">
